The paper focuses on the co-evolutionary dynamics of the blogosphere, examining the interplay between social and semantic dimensions. This suggests that the paper could fit into several sub-categories, including social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). However, given the emphasis on knowledge distribution and the analysis of a political blogosphere, the most likely sub-category is social and information networks (cs.SI).
